*.sage.py

# Environments
# Matches the CI deny pattern in scripts/ci/check-no-env-files.sh: bare .env,
# any .env.<x>/.env-<x>/.env_<x>/.env~ variant, and .envrc. Keep the broad
# globs and the explicit entries below in sync — the explicit ones document
# the canonical incident spellings (.env.old, .env.bak, .env.local) for
# new contributors; the globs catch backup/rotation patterns from IDEs and
# user-side tooling that don't fit the canonical shapes.
.env
.env.*
.env-*
.env_*
.env~*
.env.old
.env.bak
.env.local
.envrc
.venv
env/
venv/
ENV/
env.bak/
!.env.example
venv.bak/

# Docker Compose local overrides — `docker-compose.override.yml` is
# auto-merged by `docker compose` and SHOULD NEVER be committed (it
# would force per-operator local choices on every developer pulling the
# branch — see Gemini Code Assist review on PR #320 for the canonical
# incident). The tracked `docker-compose.yml` is the source of truth.
docker-compose.override.yml
docker-compose.override.yaml

