# Maintainer-local release-notes drafts (per release-checklist.md §7).
# Drafts live at repo root with a `release-notes-` prefix; the maintainer
# pastes the final content into the GitHub Release form, so the file
# never needs to ship in the repo.
release-notes-*.md

# Claude Code runtime state (per-session lock files, local-only settings).
# `.claude/skills/` is intentionally tracked (committed skill definitions);
# only ignore lock files + the local-settings overlay.
.claude/*.lock
.claude/settings.local.json
# Sibling git worktrees the agent harness checks out under .claude/worktrees/
# are full nested checkouts — never part of the main repo's tracked tree, and
# must be excluded from REUSE/license scans + status noise.
.claude/worktrees/
